with temp as( SELECT dept_id,count(distinct student_id) as student_ct FROM student GROUP BY dept_id ) SELECT * FROM (SELECT d.dept_name,CASE WHEN t.student_ct IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE t.student_ct END as student_number FROM department d LEFT JOIN temp t on d.dept_id=t.dept_id)a ORDER BY student_number desc,dept_name

select department.dept_name, ifnull(pr.student_number,0) as student_number from department left join (select dept_id, count(distinct student_id) as student_number from student group by dept_id) as pr on department.dept_id = pr.dept_id order by student_number desc

select dept_name, sum(case when student_id is not null then 1 else 0 end) as "student_number" from department d left outer join student s on s.dept_id = d.dept_id group by dept_name order by student_number desc, dept_name

select dept_name, ifnull(b.student_number, 0) as student_number from department a left join (select dept_id, count(student_id) as student_number from student group by dept_id) b on a.dept_id = b.dept_id order by student_number DESC, dept_name
select a.dept_name, count(b.student_id) as student_number from department a left join student b on a.dept_id = b.dept_id group by 1 order by 2 desc, 1

WITH students (dept_id, student_number) as (SELECT dept_id, COUNT(*) as student_number FROM student GROUP BY dept_id) SELECT d.dept_name, COALESCE(s.student_number,0) as student_number FROM students as s RIGHT JOIN department as d ON s.dept_id = d.dept_id ORDER BY student_number DESC
